    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "`<C-\\><C-n>` (or the suggested tmapping) does not close the terminal. As of this time, there is no way to exit the terminal without just quitting nvim. \r\n\r\n- `nvim --version`: v0.2.3-dev\r\n- Vim (version: ) behaves differently?\r\n- Operating system/version: macOS 10.13.3\r\n- Terminal name/version: iTerm2 Build 3.1.6beta3 (also tested on Terminal.app Version 2.8 (400))\r\n- `$TERM`: xterm-256color-italic\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce using `nvim -u NORC`\r\nEnter terminal with `:terminal` command. Attempt to exit with `<C-\\><C-n>`.\r\n\r\n### Actual behaviour\r\nThe terminal session does nothing, no feedback is given.\r\n\r\n### Expected behaviour\r\nThe terminal session to close .\r\n",
