            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "It's not supposed to close the terminal.\r\n\r\n1. `:terminal` opens a terminal buffer in normal mode.\r\n1. <kbd>i</kbd> switches to terminal mode.\r\n1. <kbd>ctrl</kbd>+<kbd>\\\\</kbd>, <kbd>ctrl</kbd>+<kbd>n</kbd> leaves terminal mode again.\r\n1. Then you close the window like any other Vim window.",
